   3 from .api import loads
   4 from .toml_document import TOMLDocument

   7 class TOMLFile(object):
   8     """
   9     Represents a TOML file.
  10     """
  11 
  12     def __init__(self, path):  # type: (str) -> None
  13         self._path = path
  14 
  15     def read(self):  # type: () -> TOMLDocument
  16         with io.open(self._path, encoding="utf-8") as f:
  17             return loads(f.read())
  18 
  19     def write(self, data):  # type: (TOMLDocument) -> None
  20         with io.open(self._path, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
  21             f.write(data.as_string())
